<H2><b>Appellate Practice</b></H2><P>
</CENTER>

Faegre & Benson has extensive experience representing clients in appeals involving significant cases in virtually every area of law.   Firm lawyers concentrating in appellate practice have regularly appeared and successfully represented clients in state and federal appellate courts including the United States Supreme Court, the United States Courts of Appeals for the Sixth, Seventh, Eighth and Ninth Circuits, the Minnesota Court of Appeals and Supreme Court, and the state appellate courts of Wisconsin, North Dakota, South Dakota, Iowa and Colorado.<p>

Firm lawyers concentrating in appellate practice have frequently assumed the handling of significant cases on appeal for the purposes of sustaining or overturning adverse verdicts and judgments, preparing petitions for review or certiorari, preparing briefs for parties and amici, and for presentation of oral argument to the appellate courts.<p>

Significant cases representing the firm's experience in appellate practice include the following:<p>

<UL>
<LI>Lujan v. Defenders of Wildlife, 504 U.S. ___, 112 S. Ct. 2130 (1992) (Endangered Species Act)<P>
<LI>Cohen v. Cowles Media Company, 501 U.S. 663 (1991) (first amendment law)<P>
<LI>H.J. Inc. v. Northwestern Bell Telephone Co., 492 U.S. 229 (1989), dismissed on remand, 734 F. Supp. 879 (D. Minn. 1990), aff'd, 954 F.2d 485 (8th Cir.), cert. denied, 504 U.S.    , 112 S.Ct. 2306 (1992) (RICO)<P>
<LI>Norwest Bank Worthington v. Ahlers,  485 U.S. 197 (1988) (bankruptcy)<P>
<LI>Minneapolis Star and Tribune Co. v. Minnesota Commissioner of Revenue, 460 U.S. 575 (1983) (first amendment challenge to state tax statute)<P>
<LI>Pree v. Brunswick Corporation, 983 F.2d 863 (8th Cir. 1992) (product liability)<P>
<LI>St. Paul Fire & Marine Insurance Company v. Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation, 968 F.2d 695 (8th Cir. 1992) (insurance coverage)<P>
<LI>United States Fire Insurance Company v. Goodyear Tire & Rubber Co., 920 F.2d 487 (8th Cir. 1990) (insurance coverage)<P>
<LI>Powell v. National Football League, 888 F.2d 559 (8th Cir. 1988) (antitrust)<P>
<LI>Drake v. Honeywell, Inc., 797 F.2d 603 (8th Cir. 1986) (Consumer Product Safety Act)<P>
<LI>AWG Farms v. Federal Crop Insurance Corporation, 757 F.2d 720 (8th Cir. 1985) (insurance coverage)<P>
<LI>Cambridge State Bank v. James, 514 N.W.2d 565 (MInn. 1994) (on remand from U.S. Supreme Court; largest tax refund case in Minnesota history)<P>
<LI>P.J. Acquisition Corp. v. Skoglund, 453 N.W.2d (Minn.1990) (Minnesota Vikings' ownership litigation)<P>
<LI>Bergquist v. Medtronic, Inc., 379 N.W.2d 508 (Minn. 1986) (product liability)<P>
<LI>Archer-Daniels-Midland Co. v. Minnesota, 315 N.W.2d 597 (Minn. 1982) (constitutional challenge to state tax statute)<P>
<LI>Superwood Corp. v. Siempelkamp Corp., 311 N.W.2d 159 (MInn. 1981) (product liability)<P>
</UL>

