<h4>International Practice and Experience</h4>

The Faegre & Benson Construction Law Practice Group is recognized internationally for legal work on major construction projects and disputes.

<UL TYPE=disc>
<LI>The firm's construction lawyers have handled cases with claims totaling hundreds of millions of dollars, serve as lead counsel in dispute proceedings venued in the United States and work with foreign counsel in proceedings overseas.
<p>
<li>The firm's construction clients include all participants in the construction process:  Owners, contractors, subcontractors, sureties, insurers, architects, engineers, project managers, construction managers, materials suppliers, permanent lenders and construction lenders.
<p>
<li>The firm's construction representation includes all types of construction above and below ground:  Manufacturing and production facilities, highways, bridges, hospitals, wastewater treatment plants, civic and convention centers, high-rise office and apartment buildings, parking ramps, tunnels, sewers, subways, and other systems.
<p>
<li>The firm's international practice is worldwide.
<p>
<li>The firm's construction experience covers the spectrum of legal issues arising out of the construction process, real estate development, contracting for design and construction services, risk management approaches to insurance and suretyship, and resolution of construction disputes through litigation, mediation, and arbitration.  The firm's lawyers have to their credit numerous reported law decisions involving construction.  
<p>
<li>The firm has relationships with outstanding engineering and construction professionals who serve as expert witnesses on technical issues.
<p>
<li>The firm is organized for efficient and effective service to the client.  The firm maintains an extensive construction law library, on-line legal information systems, and internal computerized document control systems.
</ul>

