<H2>Employee Benefits and Executive Compensation</H2>
</CENTER>
<p>
<H4>Overview of Our Practice</H4>
<P>
Faegre &amp; Benson has one of the nation's larger groups of lawyers specializing in the law of employee benefits and executive compensation.  Our size and the diversity of our experience derived from a large client base enable us to respond to the needs of a broad range of clients.  Although we primarily represent employers, we also have extensive experience in working with providers of financial products and services such as bank trust departments, insurance companies, and brokerage firms.
<P>



Because of the many applicable laws and regulations, we are involved in most aspects of benefit and compensation planning.  We assist clients with strategic planning, including developing plan specifications, initial plan design, and seeking legislative and regulatory solutions to clients' problems.  We prepare plan documents, summary plan descriptions, and other employee communications.  We counsel clients regarding the implementation and ongoing administration of benefit programs.  
<P>


Our lawyers are experienced in dealing with the Internal Revenue Service, the Department of Labor, and the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation, both in obtaining approvals of plans and transactions and in handling other tax and regulatory matters.  In addition, we deal regularly with issues involving employee benefits that arise under the securities laws, federal and state discrimination laws, state insurance laws, and federal and state wage-hour laws.
<P>


Our Washington D.C. office provides us with a unique capacity to assist clients on complicated employee benefits issues.  The staff in that office has a strong background on legislative and regulatory matters involving employee benefits.  They are acquainted with the key Congressional and agency personnel who deal with employee benefits.
<P>


Lawyers in our Employee Benefits Group and lawyers in our Litigation Group also have experience in ERISA and other types of litigation involving employee benefit plans.
<p>
