<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Family and Closely Held Businesses</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000">
<basefont size=3>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="intel3.gif"><P>

<H2>Family and Closely Held Businesses</H2>
</CENTER>
<p>
<H4>Overview of Our Practice</H4>
<P>
Faegre & Benson provides a comprehensive approach to the interrelated legal and succession planning issues that uniquely affect family and other closely held businesses.  Through its Family and Closely Held Business practice, Faegre & Benson brings together experts in corporate finance, estate planning, federal and state taxation, employee benefits, employment law, environmental law and other areas of legal specialization.  These experts work together as a team toward a common purpose:  providing family and closely held businesses, and their owners, with the highest quality legal services in a cost-effective and accessible manner.

<p>

<H4>Tailored to Distinctive Business Concerns</H4> 

The team approach is essential with family and closely held businesses.  Many decisions at the corporate level of a family or closely held business directly impact the estate and tax plans of the owners.  Employee benefits concerns have to be addressed from the perspective of the needs of the company and its ownership structure.  Employment law and many litigation issues often have distinctive problems when they arise in the family or closely held business setting.

<p>

Our experts bring experience not only in their areas of expertise, but also in working for family and closely held businesses.  The following are a few representative matters which have involved members of Faegre & Benson's Family and Closely Held Business practice:

<UL>
<LI><LI>Restructured the corporate succession plans of a mid-sized retail company with a limited number of family owners.  Issues included identifying members of the next generation having the talent and interest to take over the company, addressing the needs of other members of the next generation, adequately providing for the current generation, recapitalizing the company, revising buy-sell agreements and estate plans and ensuring a smooth transition.
<LI>Negotiated the sale of a large family controlled business in a manner that achieved optimal estate planning and tax benefits.
<LI>Drafted specifically tailored profit sharing and 401(k) plans for mid-sized firms having significant shareholders as employees.

</UL>




<H4>Demonstrated Leadership</H4>

Faegre & Benson is proud to be a principal sponsor of the Family Enterprise Forum at the University of St. Thomas Graduate School of Business and the Family Business Forum at Iowa State University.  Members of the firm's Family and Closely Held Business practice are frequent speakers at seminars on issues of particular importance to family and other closely held businesses.

<P>

