<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000">
<basefone size=3>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="intel3.gif"><P>

<H2>Health Law</H2><P>
</CENTER>

Faegre & Bensons Health Law Practice actively represents all types of health care providers including large hospital systems, physician clinics, physician organizations, joint ventures among providers, managed care organizations, and third party payor organizations.  In this era of health care reform and consolidation, Faegre & Bensons health care lawyers advise clients in connection with complicated regulatory, statutory and strategic planning matters.  Our health care lawyers have assisted clients in understanding and participating in the rapid consolidation and integration occurring in the regional and national market place by advising them in the specific areas of antitrust, tax, state and federal regulation, reimbursement, employee matters and other such areas.
<p>
<b>Group Description</b>
<br>
Faegre & Bensons health law practice is staffed by five lawyers who spend all of their time representing health care organizations.  Jay Christiansen, the partner in charge of the health law practice, Valerie Welch and Thomas Schroeder are located in the Minneapolis office.  Gerald Niederman and Laury Bowman are located in the Denver office.  In addition, the health law practice is regularly supported by the expertise of lawyers in our Exempt Organization, Corporate Finance, Employee Benefits, Governmental Affairs, Labor and Employment Law, Real Estate, Environmental, Tax and Antitrust Litigation practice groups.  In addition, Faegre & Bensons Washington D.C. lawyers monitor proposed legislation, rules and regulations; represent clients before legislative and administrative bodies; and provide clients with periodic assessments of the legislative and regulatory climate in Washington.
<p>
<b>Representative Projects</b>
<br>
Faegre & Bensons health lawyers have participated in innovative projects including the following:
<p>
<UL>
<LI>In Minnesota, Faegre & Benson obtained the first, and to date only, exemption under the States antitrust exemption process.
<p>
<LI>Faegre & Benson has represented clients in creating one of the nations largest non-profit hospital/physician/HMO systems.  
<p>
<LI>Faegre & Benson is representing a number of physicians and hospitals in the formation of integrated systems such as Physician Organizations (POs), Physician-Hospital Organizations (PHOs), clinics without walls, and managed service organizations (MSOs).
<p>
<LI>Faegre & Benson is representing clients in acquisition negotiations with for profit health care systems.
</UL>

<p>
<b>Markets Served</b>
<br>
Faegre & Bensons health law practice is active in many states including the following:<p>
<ul type=sphere>
  <li>Minnesota
  <li>Colorado
  <li>Iowa
  <li>North Dakota
  <li>South Dakota
  <li>Wisconsin
  <li>Montana
  <li>Idaho
  <li>Nebraska
  <li>Kansas
  <li>Wyoming
  <li>Missouri
  <li>New Mexico
</ul>
<p>

