<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000"><BASEFONT SIZE=3>




<CENTER><IMG SRC="labor1.gif" WIDTH=525 HEIGHT=109><P>

<H2><b>Labor and Employment Law</b></H2><P>
</CENTER>


The firm's labor and employment lawyers represent private and public employers of all sizes in the full range of issues that arise in the workplace.  We defend employers in all types of employment-related cases, such as wrongful discharge, contract, defamation, and ERISA actions.  We also defend employers against charges before the EEOC and state and local agencies and against lawsuits alleging discrimination based on age, sex (including pregnancy and sexual harassment), race, disability, and the like.  We are experienced in representing employers in the full range of alternatives to litigation, including mediations, arbitrations, and summary trials.
<p>

Using our extensive litigation experience, we counsel employers on how to avoid lawsuits and how to reduce liability should a lawsuit arise.  We assist employers in planning for and carrying out discharges, layoffs, mergers, acquisitions, and other significant employment decisions.  We deal with workplace health and safety issues, such as drug and alcohol testing, smoking, AIDS, and OSHA matters.  We also develop affirmative action plans and respond to compliance reviews.  Our attorneys review and draft personnel policies, manuals, and agreements (including noncompetition and confidentiality provisions).  We provide advice on all of the legal issues that arise in connection with personnel and compensation administration.  We also advise employers on international employment issues, such as immigration matters and questions that arise out of foreign operations.
<p>

Our lawyers represent management in union organizing campaigns, decertification elections, labor arbitration proceedings, unfair labor practice charges before the NLRB, and collective bargaining negotiations.  We help employers deal with the problems raised by picketing, handbilling, and secondary boycotts.
<p>

<h4>Representation of employers in connection with:</h4>
<p>
Wrongful discharge litigation<br>
Employment discrimination charges and litigation<br>
Employment termination disputes<br>
Organizing campaigns<br>
Decertification elections<br>
Unfair labor practice proceedings<br>
Labor arbitrations<br>
Negotiation and administration of collective bargaining agreements<br>
Strikes and other work stoppages<br>
Employment policies and practices<br>
Employee handbooks<br>
Employment contracts<br>
Non-compete and confidentiality agreements<br>
Wage-hour laws<br>
Leave laws<br>
Affirmative action plans<br>
OSHA and other workplace health issues<br>
Drug and alcohol testing<br>
Unemployment compensation<br>
Employee benefits claims and litigation<br>
Employment-related immigration matters<br>


