<H2><b>Nonprofit Law</b></H2><P>
</CENTER>

Faegre & Benson is one of a handful of law firms in the country with lawyers who work almost exclusively with nonprofit organizations.  The Nonprofit Organizations Group advises a wide variety of nonprofits, including foundations, schools, churches, social service agencies, arts organizations, hospitals, museums, and environmental groups, as well as trade associations and taxable nonprofits.
<br>
Although nonprofit organizations once were able to avoid many of the complex legal issues faced by commercial businesses, they now are in many respects held to a higher standard and subject to extensive scrutiny and government regulation.  By focusing on the unique legal needs of the nonprofit sector, the Nonprofit Organizations Group strives to provide informed and practical advice to its clients.  Group members monitor activity in the nonprofit sector daily and notify clients of important developments through periodic Issue Updates.
<br>
Members of the Nonprofit Organizations Group also call on other lawyers at Faegre & Benson to advise nonprofit clients on employment, tax exempt financing, real estate, environmental, employee benefits, government relations, and litigation matters.
<p>
<font="+2"><b>Representative Services
</b></font>
<br>
Examples of services provided by the Nonprofit Organizations Group include the following:
<P>
<UL>

<LI>Corporate reorganizations for Evangelical Lutheran Church in America, Minnesota Public Radio, LifeSpan Inc., and Health System Minnesota.
<P>
<LI>Representation of a sheltered workshop facility in the appeal of an unrelated business income tax assessment in excess of $500,000.
<P>
<LI>Developing risk management programs and advising nonprofit clients in crisis situations to minimize liability.
<P>
<LI>Advising charities about the tax  and non-tax aspects of charitable contributions.
<P>
<LI>Assisting charities in the structuring and administration of deferred giving programs.
<P>
<LI>Advising boards of directors about their fiduciary duties, conflicts of interest, and director and officer liability insurance.
<P>
<LI>General representation of community foundations.
<P>
<LI>Preparing employee and volunteer screening programs for nonprofits working with vulnerable clients.
<P>
<LI>Incorporating and obtaining tax exempt status for new organizations.
<P>
<LI>Advising private foundations on minimum payout requirements, taxable expenditures, and self-dealing rules.
<P>
<LI>Preparing sexual harassment, sexual violence, student misconduct, and disciplinary policies and procedures.
<P>
<LI>Advising charities on issues relating to private inurement, private benefit, lobbying and political activities.
<P>
<LI>Preparing state securities and insurance registrations for pooled income funds and charitable gift annuity programs.
<P>
<LI>Obtaining court approval of deviations from terms of charitable trusts.
<P>
<LI>Advising charities on the administration of endowment funds and restricted gifts.
</UL>


Members of the Nonprofit Organizations Group participated in the drafting of the Minnesota Nonprofit Corporations Act, teach courses on nonprofit law, and serve on the boards of many nonprofit organizations.
<p>

<font="+2"><b>Faegre & Benson
</b></font>
<br>
Faegre & Benson is a firm of over 270 lawyers, with offices in Minneapolis, Denver, Washington, D.C., Des Moines, London, and Frankfurt.  The firm advises clients of virtually all sizes on a wide variety of matters.  Faegre & Benson has a long history of service to the community and is proud to represent many of the regions leading nonprofit institutions.

<p>

