<H2>Minneapolis, Minnesota</H2>
</CENTER>

For more than one hundred years, Faegre & Benson has provided legal services to businesses and individuals from its offices in Minneapolis.  Some of the firm's first clients were the milling and lumber companies which lead to the growth of the early Twin Cities' economy.  Now the firm represents companies from all sections of the regional and national economy, including the region's largest bank, the region's largest merchant, several of its largest hospitals, many other of the region's leading manufacturing, agricultural and service businesses and a number of Fortune 500 companies.  Faegre & Benson also serves as legal counsel for many of the region's leading civic, cultural and educational institutions, and a number of its individual lawyers play important roles in the governance of these institutions.<p>

As a result of the firm's long-time representation of Minnesota companies and its continuing involvement in the civic life of the region, Faegre & Benson provides its clients not only with sophisticated legal services in virtually every area of civil law, but provides these services with a practical understanding of the needs and wants of Minnesota clients.  The Minneapolis office, with more than 200 resident lawyers, serves as a center for the firm's other offices, making available to clients at all locations the legal resources of the entire firm.<p>

Faegre & Benson<BR>
2200 Norwest Center<BR>
90 South Seventh Street<BR>
Minneapolis, Minnesota  55402 3901<BR>
612-336-3000<P>

