<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000">
<BASEFONT SIZE=3>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="ban_lond.gif"><P>

<H2>London, England</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>

Faegre & Benson<BR>
10 Eastcheap<BR>
London EC3M 1ET, England<BR>
44 171 623 6163

<P>

Faegre & Benson established a London office in 1985 to assist clients who wanted experienced yet familiar representation in their dealings in the United Kingdom and elsewhere in Europe.  Staffed with both American attorneys and English solicitors, the practice of the London office has expanded to meet the needs of American clients doing business in the European Union and international clients doing business in the United States.  In particular, the London office provides counsel for American companies seeking trade, investment and financing abroad and for foreign companies seeking trade, direct investment and general representation in the United States.  The London office also advises on all aspects of European Union law.<br>

<P>

The proximity of London to continental Europe and to our Frankfurt office enables the firm to provide clients with efficient and cost-effective service in the European Union, as well as in Eastern Europe.  Moreover, London's position as a gateway to Europe, and as a leading banking and financial center, makes it a preferred location for international financial transactions.<br>

<P>

The Firm's lawyers in London regularly work with the lawyers in our other offices and are able to draw upon the skills and experience of all the Firm's practice areas.  In matters involving Central and Eastern Europe, the London office works closely with our office in Frankfurt.<P>


<P>

