<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="ban_frnk.gif"><P>

<H2>Frankfurt, Germany</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>

Faegre & Benson<BR>
Weisenau 1<BR>
60323 Frankfurt am Main, Germany<BR>
49 69 971 227 0

<p>

Even before the Berlin Wall came down in November 1989, Faegre & Benson's lawyers were active in the countries of Central and Eastern Europe on behalf of our clients.  After the Wall came down, the scope of our practice in these countries continued to expand and, in response, Faegre & Benson opened an office in Frankfurt in 1991.  The office has both American and German attorneys on staff.

<p>

The purpose of the Frankfurt office is to serve the growing needs of clients in connection with established business operations in Germany and the rest of the European Union.  The office also assists clients seeking to initiate or increase their investments in Central and Eastern Europe and in the Commonwealth of Independent States.  Frankfurt, which is a principal European hub for air travel and one of Europe's financial centers, provides a centralized base for the firm's European work.

<p>

The Frankfurt office works closely with Faegre & Benson's London and United States offices in handling and coordinating international business matters.

<P>

<A HREF="att_frnk.html">Attorneys</A>

<P>

