<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000">
<BASEFONT SIZE=3>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="office3.gif"><P>

<H2>Almaty, Kazakstan</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
Faegre & Benson<BR>
597 Seifullin Street<BR>
Suite 300<BR>
480072 Almaty, Kazakstan<BR>
7 3272 64 79 79

<P>

Faegre & Benson's Almaty office has a multinational business-oriented practice that specializes in providing assistance to individuals and companies doing business or investing in the Republic of Kazakstan and the other Central Asian Republics of the former Soviet Union.

<p>

Because the Almaty office is comprised of American and Kazak attorneys, it can perform a wide range of services for foreign investors and businesses, such as:

<p>

<UL>

<LI>Advice and information concerning the laws of Kazakstan pertaining to foreign investments, taxation, foreign currency regulations, privatization, customs regulations, and labor law.
<P>
<LI>Drafting of documents for the formation and operation of joint ventures.
<P>
<LI>Preparation of incorporation documents.
<P>
<LI>Assistance in connection with the registration of branch offices of foreign enterprises.
<P>
<LI>Assistance in acquiring and extending ordinary and multiple-entry visas.
</UL>


Current clients of our Almaty office include the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development (U.K.), Mobil Oil Corporation (U.S.), ABN Amro Bank (The Netherlands), VEBA Öl AG (Germany) and the International Finance Corporation (U.S.). 

<p>

The Firm also performs legal services outside of Kazakstan on behalf of Kazak businesses with foreign  commercial or investment interests as well as for various units of the government of Kazakstan.

<p>

The Almaty office works closely with the Firm's London and Frankfurt offices, and draws upon the Firm's varied practice groups in the United States on a demand basis.  The office provides interpreter and translation services in the English, Russian and Kazakh languages.

<p>

<A HREF="att_almt.html">Attorneys</A>

