<H2>Bankruptcy/Insolvency
Secured Creditor Representation
</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>

<blockquote>
In large bankruptcies of publicly-held corporations, in smaller reorganizations, in complex bankruptcies involving individuals and partnerships, in out-of-court work-outs and restructurings, and in foreclosures and other enforcement proceedings, Faegre & Benson brings experience, skill and strength to the representation of secured creditors interests.  Our lawyers' experience on both the transactional and bankruptcy/work-out sides of secured financing provides the depth and perspective essential for effective representation.  We have represented major banks, small community banks, indenture trustees, insurance companies and other financial institutions.  Our clients include:

<UL>
<LI>Norwest Corporation
<LI>Norwest Bank Minnesota, N.A. and other Norwest affiliates
<LI>TCF Bank Savings fsb
<LI>Chemical Bank
<LI>Rabobank Nederland
<LI>Continental Bank
<LI>The Mitsubishi Bank, Ltd.
<LI>National City Bank of Minneapolis
<LI>The St. Paul Bank for Cooperatives
<LI>Federal Land Bank of St. Paul, Farm Credit Services, and Agribank
<LI>Northwestern National Life Insurance Company and  affiliates
<LI>Washington Square Capital, Inc.
<LI>The Prudential Life Insurance Company of America
<LI>Prudential Capital Corporation
<LI>The Principal Mutual Life Insurance Company
<LI>IDS Financial Services
<LI>IDS Life Insurance Company
<LI>The Travelers Insurance Company
<LI>John Hancock Mutual Insurance Company
<LI>The Mutual Life Insurance Company 	of New York
<LI>Massachusetts Mutual Life Insurance 	Company
<LI>BankAmerica Business Credit, Inc.
<LI>Diversified Business Credit, Inc.
</UL>

Our lawyers have negotiated successful restructurings outside of bankruptcy as well as consensual plans of reorganization in Chapter 11 proceedings.  Faegre & Benson and its affiliate, The Faegre Group, are strong supporters of--and have considerable experience in--alternative dispute resolution.
<p>

Although we believe most restructurings and bankruptcy matters are best resolved through effective negotiation, when necessary our lawyers pursue appropriate litigation remedies.  Faegre & Benson lawyers have gone to the United States Supreme Court and won the leading bankruptcy case which recognizes the right of creditors to prevent equity holders from retaining their interests over the objection of unpaid creditors--a principal known as the "absolute priority rule."  Other significant bankruptcy litigation has included claim classification disputes, valuation of collateral, commercial reasonableness of proposed debt restructuring terms, as well as relief from stay and case dismissal proceedings.  In addition, our lawyers have obtained confirmation of a creditors plan over the debtors competing plan and objections in a real estate partnership case.  We also have considerable experience and expertise in state court repossession and foreclosure proceedings.
<p>

Representative significant cases in which our lawyers have participated on behalf of secured creditor or indenture trustee clients include:

<UL>
<LI>Bonneville Pacific Corporation (D. Utah)
<LI>Reserve Mining Company [LTV Steel] 	(S.D.N.Y.)
<LI>Interco Incorporated (E.D. Mo.)
<LI>American Continental Corporation (D. Ariz.)
<LI>Savin Corporation (S.D.N.Y.)
<LI>Generra Sportswear Company, Inc. W.D. Wash.)
<LI>KLH Computers, Inc. (N.D. Tex.)
<LI>Brutger Equities, Inc. (D. Minn.)
<LI>Insilco Corporation (W. D. Tex.)
<LI>Lampert Lumber Company (D. Minn.)
