<LI>Advance United Expressways (D. Minn.)
<LI>Brown & Bigelow (D. Minn.)
<LI>Bucyrus Erie Company (E. D. Wisc.)
<LI>MEI Diversified, Inc. (D. Minn.)
</UL>


Effective representation of secured creditors in bankruptcy or out-of-court restructurings frequently requires more than bankruptcy and transactional expertise.  The breadth and strength of our law firm permits our bankruptcy/insolvency lawyers to draw upon diverse experience in numerous complex legal areas which arise in the course of a bankruptcy proceeding or work-out.  Our lawyers experience in creditor litigation, tax, real estate, leasing, mergers and acquisitions, shareholder and officer/director litigation, lender and professional liability matters, environmental regulation, employee benefits, ERISA, labor law, insurance coverage issues, intellectual property, securitization, governmental relations and many other matters enables our bankruptcy/insolvency lawyers to provide virtually any area of legal expertise as the need may arise in their representation of secured creditors.
<p>

Our bankruptcy representation is not limited to secured creditor representation.  In various significant matters, Faegre & Benson has represented debtors, unsecured creditors, equity holders, committees, lessors, licensors of intellectual property rights, and other interests.  This experience enhances our ability to provide effective representation of secured creditors because the diverse experience in bankruptcy/insolvency matters gives our lawyers judgment and insight; for example, our experience in representing unsecured creditors and committees provides insight respecting the expectations -- and weaknesses -- of those interests.  Our lawyers' representation of debtors in several major Chapter 11 cases similarly provides insight from the debtor's side of the table in plan negotiation and other aspects of bankruptcy reorganization.

</blockquote>
