<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> Airports, Baseball Stadiums and Convention Centers</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000">
<basefont size=3>

<H2>Airports, Baseball Stadiums and Convention Centers</H2>

<H4>by</H4>

<h4>Faegre & Benson Government Relations Team</h4>
<p>



<strong>Minneapolis/St. Paul Airport</strong><br>

<FONT SIZE=+2>T</FONT>here was significant debate this session over expansion of the Minneapolis/St. Paul International Airport or construction of a new airport in Dakota County.<p>

Legislation prohibiting construction of a new airport in Dakota County and outlining the parameters for expansion of the existing airport ignited heated debate on the floors of the Senate and House.  This legislation was ultimately adopted by the Legislature and signed into law (Chapter 464.)<p>

<strong>New Baseball Stadium</strong><br>

A proposal to place a non-binding referendum on the 1996 general election ballot in the Twin Cities area received significant media exposure this year, but made little legislative progress.  The proposed referendum question asked voters whether the Legislature should provide for the construction of a new baseball stadium with a retractable roof using private money and hospitality taxes.<p>

Although the bill died in the middle of session, an interim legislative task force of legislators, business leaders and representatives of Minnesota sports franchises is expected to work on a proposal for construction and financing of a new baseball stadium to be presented to the 1997 Legislature.<P>

<strong>Minneapolis Convention Center</strong><br>

Governor Carlson vetoed $13 million to get started on a $160 million expansion of the Minneapolis Convention Center.  He said sufficient planning had not been done.<p>

The Governor is attempting to assemble a package of public projects, including the Convention Center expansion, for passage in 1997.
<P>

<font="+2"><b>Questions</b></font><br>

If you have any questions, please contact Rich Forschler at <A HREF="mailto:rforschl@faegre.com"><EM>rforschl@faegre.com</EM></A> or Bob Hentges at <A HREF="mailto:rhentges@faegre.com"><EM>rhentges@faegre.com</EM></A>. 
<p>

