<HEAD><TITLE>1997 Intellectual Property - Nuts & Bolts of Patents and Trade Secrets</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="backgrnd.gif" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#FF7F76" ALINK="#EEDFFF"><BASEFONT SIZE=4>
<TABLE cellpadding=0>
<TR>
<TD width=120><FONT SIZE=+1 face="courier">Nuts & Bolts of Patents and Trade Secrets
</FONT>
</TD>

<TD colspan=2 align=left><p align=center><IMG SRC="fb.gif" ALT="Letterhead GIF" HSPACE=25 ALIGN=absbottom><br>

<IMG SRC="clear.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=1>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td></td>

<td><IMG SRC="clear.gif" WIDTH=55 HEIGHT=10 hspace=20></TD>

<td>
<p align=left>

<FONT SIZE=+2>T</font><STRONG>rade Secrets</STRONG>:  The trade secret segment of our presentation identifies the basic parameters of trade secret law and distinguishes trade secrets from other methods of protecting intellectual property.  We then describe the elements of a trade secret protection program.  We conclude by explaining how to protect trade secrets during employee transition.
<br>
<FONT SIZE=+2>P</font><strong>atents</strong>:  The patent segment of our presentation will describe the practical aspects of patent law so that the business person can better incorporate patenting strategies into competitive business planning.  We first explain how to recognize and protect patentable inventions so that valuable patent rights are not inadvertently lost.  We then explain how patent rights can be used to help meet specific business objectives.  We conclude by providing an overview of patent enforcement procedures.
</p>
</td>
</tr>
<td>
</td>

<td colspan=2 align=center>

<A HREF="ip97.htm"><IMG SRC="invite.gif" WIDTH=66 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0></a>
