<HEAD><TITLE>1997 Intellectual Property - Nuts & Bolts of Trademarks and Copyrights</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="backgrnd.gif" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#FF7F76" ALINK="#EEDFFF"><BASEFONT SIZE=4>
<TABLE cellpadding=0>
<TR>
<TD width=120><FONT SIZE=+1 face="courier">Nuts & Bolts of Trademarks and Copyrights
</FONT>
</TD>

<TD colspan=2 align=left><p align=center><IMG SRC="fb.gif" ALT="Letterhead GIF" HSPACE=25 ALIGN=absbottom><br>

<IMG SRC="clear.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=1>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td></td>

<td><IMG SRC="clear.gif" WIDTH=55 HEIGHT=10 hspace=20></TD>

<td width=400>
<p align=left>

<FONT SIZE=+2>T</font>rademarks and copyrights can be amongst the most valuable of a business' assets.  This session will provide an overview of the law that protects these assets, with an emphasis on what business people and business lawyers need to know to maximize the value of their business' rights.  Trademark topics covered will include selection and availability of a mark, federal registration procedure, proper use of a mark, and the remedies available for trademark infringement.  Copyright topics covered will include copyrightable subject matter, copyright ownership and works for hire, copyright notice and registration, and the scope of copyright protection. 
</p>
</td>
</tr>
<td>
</td>

