<HEAD><TITLE>1997 Intellectual Property - Censorship on the Internet</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="backgrnd.gif" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#FF7F76" ALINK="#EEDFFF"><BASEFONT SIZE=4>
<TABLE cellpadding=0>
<TR>
<TD width=120><FONT SIZE=+1 face="courier">Censorship on the Internet
</FONT>
</TD>

<TD colspan=2 align=left><p align=center><IMG SRC="fb.gif" ALT="Letterhead GIF" HSPACE=25 ALIGN=absbottom><br>

<IMG SRC="clear.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=1>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td></td>

<td><IMG SRC="clear.gif" WIDTH=55 HEIGHT=10 hspace=20></TD>

<td width=400>
<p align=left>

<FONT SIZE=+2>A</font>s use of the Internet proliferates, conflicts are arising over appropriate regulation of the content of cyberspace communications.  Congress enacted the Communications Decency Act, but a court declared it unconstitutional.  An electronic bulletin board operator in California was convicted in federal court in Memphis, Tennessee, on criminal charges.  Law enforcement authorities in Germany threatened prosecution of CompuServe, an Ohio-based company, for the content of material available through CompuServes network.  In light of such developments, this seminar will provide an overview of issues related to Internet content regulation, including such issues as the First Amendment, jurisdiction, choice of law, defamation and privacy.
</p>
</td>
</tr>
<td>
</td>

<td colspan=2 align=center>

<A HREF="ip97.htm"><IMG SRC="invite.gif" WIDTH=66 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0></a>
<IMG SRC="splitter.gif" WIDTH=7 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0>

<A HREF="ip_sched.htm"> <IMG SRC="schedule.gif" WIDTH=67 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0></A>
<IMG SRC="splitter.gif" WIDTH=7 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0>

<A HREF="ip_regis.htm"> <IMG SRC="register.gif" WIDTH=77 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0></A>
<IMG SRC="splitter.gif" WIDTH=7 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0>

<A HREF="ip_topcs.htm"> <IMG SRC="topics.gif" WIDTH=49 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0></A>

<p align=center><i><font size=-1>
Copyright &copy; 1997 Faegre &amp; Benson LLP, all rights reserved.<font></i>

</p>
</td></tr></table>

</BODY>
