<HEAD><TITLE>1997 Intellectual Property - Recent Developments - Patents</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="backgrnd.gif" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#FF7F76" ALINK="#EEDFFF"><BASEFONT SIZE=4>
<TABLE cellpadding=0>
<TR>
<TD width=120><FONT SIZE=+1 face="courier">Recent Developments - Patents
</FONT>
</TD>

<TD colspan=2 align=left><p align=center><IMG SRC="fb.gif" ALT="Letterhead GIF" HSPACE=25 ALIGN=absbottom><br>

<IMG SRC="clear.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=1>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td></td>

<td><IMG SRC="clear.gif" WIDTH=55 HEIGHT=10 hspace=20></TD>

<td>
<p align=left>

<FONT SIZE=+2>S</font>ignificant new developments occurred in many areas of patent law in 1996.  These developments involved not only substantive changes in the law, but also several issues of first impression appearing in Federal Circuit decisions throughout the year. Several Federal Circuit decisions also interpreted the insubstantial differences test for determining infringement under the doctrine of equivalents, which was a test announced by the Federal Circuit in the important Hilton-Davis decision.  Meanwhile, the Hilton-Davis case itself is on appeal to the United States Supreme Court, which could render its decision at anytime now.  The patent bar eagerly awaits the Supreme Court decision to see how it will affect the test for determining infringement under the doctrine of equivalents.  A number of unusual district court decisions also appeared, which could be the harbinger of even more change in the patent laws in the event that such lower court decisions were to be upheld by the Federal Circuit on appeal. This session will provide an overview of these recent developments, so that patent attorneys and business persons alike can more fully appreciate how these developments might affect how patents can and cannot be used to support strategic business planning and meet specific business objectives.
</p>
</td>
</tr>
<td>
</td>

<td colspan=2 align=center>

<A HREF="ip97.htm"><IMG SRC="invite.gif" WIDTH=66 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0></a>
<IMG SRC="splitter.gif" WIDTH=7 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0>

<A HREF="ip_sched.htm"> <IMG SRC="schedule.gif" WIDTH=67 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0></A>
<IMG SRC="splitter.gif" WIDTH=7 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0>

<A HREF="ip_regis.htm"> <IMG SRC="register.gif" WIDTH=77 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0></A>
<IMG SRC="splitter.gif" WIDTH=7 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0>

<A HREF="ip_topcs.htm"> <IMG SRC="topics.gif" WIDTH=49 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0></A>

<p align=center><i><font size=-1>
Copyright &copy; 1997 Faegre &amp; Benson LLP, all rights reserved.<font></i>

</p>
</td></tr></table>

</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
