<HEAD><TITLE>1997 Intellectual Property - Insurance Issues in Intellectual Property Litigation</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="backgrnd.gif" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#FF7F76" ALINK="#EEDFFF"><BASEFONT SIZE=4>
<TABLE cellpadding=0>
<TR>
<TD width=120><FONT SIZE=+1 face="courier">Insurance Issues in Intellectual Property Litigation
</FONT>
</TD>

<TD colspan=2 align=left><p align=center><IMG SRC="fb.gif" ALT="Letterhead GIF" HSPACE=25 ALIGN=absbottom><br>

<IMG SRC="clear.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=1>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td></td>

<td><IMG SRC="clear.gif" WIDTH=55 HEIGHT=10 hspace=20></TD>

<td width=400>
<p align=left>

<FONT SIZE=+2>I</font>nsurance coverage for intellectual property disputes is an important consideration for litigants.  Cases that have held for both the insured and the insurer regarding the duty to defend and indemnify will be discussed, along with a brief outline of the procedural steps to be taken by insureds and insurers in the process of determining the applicability of insurance coverage.
</p>
</td>
</tr>
<td>
</td>

<td colspan=2 align=center>

<A HREF="ip97.htm"><IMG SRC="invite.gif" WIDTH=66 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0></a>
