<HEAD><TITLE>1997 Intellectual Property - Recent Developments - Copyright Law</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="backgrnd.gif" TEXT="#FFFFFF" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#FF7F76" ALINK="#EEDFFF"><BASEFONT SIZE=4>
<TABLE cellpadding=0>
<TR>
<TD width=120><FONT SIZE=+1 face="courier">Recent Developments - Copyright Law
</FONT>
</TD>

<TD colspan=2 align=left><p align=center><IMG SRC="fb.gif" ALT="Letterhead GIF" HSPACE=25 ALIGN=absbottom><br>

<IMG SRC="clear.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=1>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td></td>

<td><IMG SRC="clear.gif" WIDTH=55 HEIGHT=10 hspace=20></TD>

<td width=400>
<p align=left>

<FONT SIZE=+2>T</font>his session will explore recent developments in the law of copyrights, including recent legislation and international agreements.  The presentation will include discussion of the issue as raised in a recent Fifth Circuit case <EM>Chavez v. Arte Publico Press</EM>, 59 F.3d 539 (5th Cir. 1995).  The case is still pending reconsideration after remand from the U.S. Supreme Court subsequent to its decision in <EM>Seminole Tribe of Florida v. Florida</EM>, 517 U.S. ___, 116 S.Ct. ____, 134 L.Ed. 252 (1996), which limited Congress ability to abrogate states Eleventh Amendment sovereign immunity.  The presentation will provide background regarding why Congress cannot generally abrogate a states sovereign immunity and the limited circumstances under which it can.  It will also include a discussion of how a state might waive its immunity.  Finally, the presentation will discuss practical steps a client dealing with the state can take to protect himself or herself should the courts decide that a state may exercise their eleventh amendment sovereign immunity against copyright infringement suits brought in federal court.
</p>
</td>
</tr>
<td>
</td>

<td colspan=2 align=center>

<A HREF="ip97.htm"><IMG SRC="invite.gif" WIDTH=66 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0></a>
<IMG SRC="splitter.gif" WIDTH=7 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0>

<A HREF="ip_sched.htm"> <IMG SRC="schedule.gif" WIDTH=67 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0></A>
<IMG SRC="splitter.gif" WIDTH=7 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0>
<A HREF="ip_regis.htm"> <IMG SRC="register.gif" WIDTH=77 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0></A>
<IMG SRC="splitter.gif" WIDTH=7 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0>

<A HREF="ip_topcs.htm"> <IMG SRC="topics.gif" WIDTH=49 HEIGHT=14 hspace=0></A>

<p align=center><i><font size=-1>
Copyright &copy; 1997 Faegre &amp; Benson LLP, all rights reserved.<font></i>

</p>
</td></tr></table>

