<h1>IAI</h1>
<h2 align=center>International African Institute<br>
Institut Africain International</h2>
<h4 align=center>SOAS, Thornhaugh Street, Russell Square, <br>London WC1H OXG, UK</h4>
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>

<p align=center>
</p><!!Insert the current design of the
maps of Africa>
<h3>Resume</h3>

The International African Institute (IAI), currently based in London, was founded in 1926 as the International Institute of African Languages and Cultures. It is governed by an international council, at least one-third of whose members are nationals of African countries.

<p>The IAI sees its role today as contributing to the facilitation of communication between scholars in Africa and Africanists throughout the world, and dissemination of their research results. Particular importance is attached to scholarly dialogue across the Arabic, francophone, lusophone and anglophone regions. This role is fulfilled through supporting seminars, research and publications.

<ul><li><a href="iai_info.html">Further information about IAI and its work</a>

<li><a href="ajdp.html">African Journals Distribution Programme</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="ajdp_journals.html">AJDP - Journals & Libraries 1996</a>
<li><a href="ajdp_update.html">AJDP - Update August 1995</a></ul>

<li><a href="jouhnbk.html">Handbook of Good Practice in Journals Publishing</a>
<li><a href="iaipubs.html">IAI and its publications</a>
<li><a href="wampe.html">WAMP - West African Museums Programme</a><br><a href="wampf.html">Programme des Mus&eacute;e de l'Afrique de l'Ouest</a>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3>INTERNATIONAL AFRICAN INSTITUTE (IAI)<br>
INSTITUT AFRICAIN INTERNATIONAL (IAI)</h3>

<h4>Honorary Director: Professor Paul Spencer<br>
Director, Research and Development: Carol Priestley<br>
Chairman, Publications Committee: Dr Elizabeth Dunstan<br>
Head, Special Programmes: Diana Rosenberg<br>
General Enquiries: Pru Watts-Russell</h4>


<h3>SOAS, Thornhaugh Street, Russell Square, London WC1H OXG, UK 
