<h1 align=center>UPCOMING EVENTS</h1>

If you want more details then call or write to us at the address shown below.
<p>

<b>United Kingdom</b>
<p>

<p><li>LONDON: 10th January marks the second month since the
murder of Ken and the eight other Ogoni activists. We will remember them and protest against the trial of the following 19 Ogonis between 12.00 and 2.00pm outside the Nigeria High Commission, 9 Northumberland Avenue. 

<p><li>GLASGOW: 15th, 19th or 26th January - A discussion evening
will be held on the Ogoni issues.

<p><li>LONDON: 17th January - The National Theatre at the Barbican
Centre is putting on one of Ken Saro-Wiwa's plays. 

<p><li>OXFORD: 19th January - As part of Oxford City Council's
'Festival of Black Culture' there will be an event focusing on the Ogoni issues. At the Pegasus Theatre, Tel: 01865 249811.

<p><li>LONDON: 20th or 27th January - a one day forum will be held
to examine the prospects for a new world order based on the democratic right of the 'poor and powerless' to actively participate in the decision-making process.... Caxton House, 129 St. John's Way, Islington N19 3RQ, Tel: 0171-263 3151.

<p><li>LONDON: 23rd or 24th January - A lecture entitled "Africa -
the way forward' will be given by a well-known Ogoni figure at Holborn College, 200 Greyhound Road W14 9RL, Tel: 0171-385 3377.

<p><li>OXFORD: 24th January - Diana Wiwa will be taking part in
discussions as part of Greenscreen's environmental film festival from 24th to 27th January.

<p><li>YORK: 26th January - the students at York University are
organising an event at the Global and International Centre. 

<p><li>CAMBRIDGE: 31st January - Long Road 6th Form College are
organising an equal opportunities morning looking at the environmental damage and the situation in Nigeria. Tel: 01223-247810.

<p><li>OXFORD: 1st February - The University of Oxford Union are
holding a debate on democracy in developing countries. 

<p><li>DERBY: 15th February - the University of Derby, Faculty of
European and International Studies is holding a lecture on Ogoni which will be presented by the General Secretary of OCA-UK and Mr. Douglas, a Nigerian Human Rights campaigner. 

<p><li>MAIL ORDER: There is a limited edition copy of a dance mix
CD which has been made in memory of Ken Saro-Wiwa, available on mail-order. Please check the Greenpeace w.w.w.-site for the address.

<p><b>Outside the UK</b>

<p><li>OLDENBURG, GERMANY: 2/3 or 9/10 February - there is a
symposium taking place on the socio-political developments in Nigeria being organised by Dr. Gottfried Mergner of the Institut fuer Bildung und Kommunikation in Migrationprozessen (IBKM) at Universitaet Oldenburg, 0441- 798-2040.

<p><li>DERRY, NORTHERN IRELAND: February/March - there is a
possible speakers tour being organised in the area. Watch this space.

<p><li>NUERNBERG, GERMANY: January/February - Stadt Nuernberg
supported by the Faculty of African Studies at the University of Bayreuth will be campaigning for the Ogoni. Contact Dorit Bruenesholz, tel: 231-3165 

<p>
Finally, if you are organising an event (seminar, talk or whatever) or know someone who is doing so then please let us know so that we can let everyone else know.


