<hr>
<h1 align=center>The Ogoni Community Association</h1>

The Ogoni Community Association - United Kingdom was set up in 1993 by Ogoni people living in Britain as an affiliate of the Movement for the survival of Ogoni people.

<p>Its remit is to focus world attention on the plight of the Ogoni people throughout peaceful and non-violent campaigning and to support and promote their emancipation through the Ogoni Bill of Rights adopted by general acclaim of the Ogoni people on the 26th day of August, 1990 at Bori, Rivers State.

<h1 align=center>The Ogoni Foundation</h1>
<h3 align=center>Charity Registration Number: 1050502</h3>
The Ogoni Foundation has been set up to relieve poverty and sickness by appropriate charitable (whether medical rehabilitation, financial or other) assistance in any part of the world and in particular (but without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing) by the provision of aid to the needy in Nigeria of persons formerly resident there. It also aims to advance the education of people living in the United Kingdom and Nigeria in the Ogoni languages, traditions and cultures by the provision of a Saturday school.  Finally, it will help to protect and preserve the environment in Africa and other parts of the world by the provision of educational leaflets and projects and by assisting the local conservation projects.
<hr>
<h3 align=center>The Ogoni Community Association - UK</h3>
<h4 align=center>3-4 Albion Place, London, W6 0LT. Tel: 0181 563 8614 Fax: 0181 563 8615</h4>
<hr>
