<html>
<head>
<title> Publications</title>
<!!keys: >
</HEAD>
<FRAMESET COLS="195,*">

<FRAMESET ROWS="95, *">
<FRAME SCROLLING="no" NAME="top" NORESIZE SRC="../logo.html">
<FRAME SCROLLING="auto" NAME="middle" NORESIZE SRC="banner.html">
</FRAMESET>
<FRAME SCROLLING="yes" NAME="right" SRC="pubs.html">
</FRAMESET>

<NOFRAMES>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#000066" vlink="#FF6600">
<a href="../info/index.html"><img src="../pix/logo-t.gif" width=96 height=41 hspace=10
vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a>
<h6 align=left>The material that follows has been provided by <a
href="../info/index.html">ACTIONAID</a></h6><br clear=right>
<br>
<h2 align=center>Publications </h2>

ACTIONAID publishes <b><a href="#reports">reports</a></b> and <b><a href="#brief">briefings</a></b>
on poverty issues for specialist and general audiences. Publications can be ordered by post by
printing the <b><a href="order.html">order form</a></b>.


<h3>Reports </h3>
<img src="26.jpg" align=left hspace=10 vspace=3 width=150 height=209 border=1>
<b>1. The Reflect Mother Manual</b><br>
David Archer & Sara Cottingham 1996.
<p>

The Reflect Mother Manual is a detailed and practical guide to a new approach to adult literacy which 
radically re-defines the role of adult literacy in social change. In a Reflect programme there is no
textbook or primer, only a facilitator's manual. Each literacy circle develops its own  learning
materials though the construction of maps, matrices, calendars and diagrams. The Mother Manual is
primarily aimed at education co-ordinators and advisors in grassroots organisations, NGOs, national,
regional and local governments who are planning a literacy programme. It will also be of interest to
a wider group of development practitioners, policy makers donors and academics. 
<p>
<font face=arial, helvetica size=4><b><a
href="http://www.oneworld.org/actionaid/movs/reflect.mov">Discover what Overseas Development Minister
Baroness Lynda Chalker says about Reflect</a></b><small>[Video clip:]</font><p>

<b>£10.00</b>
<br clear=left>
<p>

<img src="1.jpg" align=left hspace=10 vspace=3 width=150 height=268 border=1>
<a name="report"></a>
<b>2. Listening to Smaller Voices</b><p>


This report, based on significant research into the roles of children in developing countries,
concludes that children make a substantial contribution to the workloads of households - in the home
itself, in the field and through remittances for wage labour. Instead of being "seen and not heard",
children should be brought into the process of development planning, implementation and evaluation.

<p>
<b>£8.00</b>

<p>
<i>(Shorter briefing also available - see <b><a href="#brief7">Briefings 7</a></b>)</i>
<br clear=left>
<p>

<img src="2.jpg" align=left hspace=10 vspace=3 width=150 height=197 border=1>

<b>3. Reality of Aid 1995</b>
 
<p>
Available from Earthscan. For more information, see <b><a href="../news/realaid.html">the bleakest
picture in a generation</a></b>.

<br clear=left>
<p>

<img src="3.jpg" align=left hspace=10 vspace=3 width=150 height=200 border=1>

<b>4. Lifestyle Overload? Population and Environment in the Balance</b>

<p>
A report of the ACTIONAID seminar held in 1991 in the run up to the Earth Summit in Brazil. Edited by
Victoria Johnson

<p>
<b>£2.95</b>


<br clear=left>
<p>

<img src="4.jpg" align=left hspace=10 vspace=3 width=150 height=202 border=1>

<b>5. Preparing the Future - Women </b><br>
Literacy and Development, Professor Lalage Bown 1990.  
 
<p>
Reissued for International Year of the Family. Looks at the impact of female 
literacy on human development and the participation of literate women in change.

<p>
<b>£5.50</b>


<br clear=left>
<p>

<img src="5.jpg" align=left hspace=10 vspace=3 width=150 height=225 border=1>

<b>6. Aid for the Poorest? UK Aid to Bangladesh </b><br>
Dr Mark Robinson ODI, 1988.

<p>
The needs of the most vulnerable groups are highlighted in this contribution to the debate about the
objectives and 
performance of British Aid.

<p>
<b>£2.00</b>

<br clear=left>
<p>

<img src="6.jpg" align=left hspace=10 vspace=3 width=150 height=207 border=1>

<b>7. Poverty-Focused Aid: The Lessons of Experience</b><br> Professor Paul Mosley, 1987.  

<p>
ACTIONAID was among the first 
agencies to draw attention to the failure of much aid to reach the poorest people.  This report
details the experiences of both official aid donors and voluntary 
organisations in surmounting the 
difficulties of targeting aid.

<p>
<b>£2.00</b>
<br clear=left>
<hr>
<a name="brief"></a>
<h3>Briefings </h3>


<b>Individually - £2.00	    Full set - £12.00</b>
<p>
<ul>

<img src="7.jpg" align=left hspace=10 vspace=3 width=150 height=231 border=1>

<b>1. The Changing Face of Aid</b><br>
Summary of Reality of Aid 1994, 
highlighting key issues on aid levels, 
aid dilution and European Aid.
<br clear=left>
<p>

<img src="8.jpg" align=left hspace=10 vspace=3 width=150 height=213 border=1>

<b>2. The Roots of Reconciliation </b><br>
Summary of 'Peacemaking endeavours of 
contemporary lineage leaders: A survey of grassroots peace conferences in 
North-West  Somalia/Somaliland'.
Dr Ahmed Yusuf Farah with 
Professor I. M. Lewis. December 1993.
<br clear=left>
<p>

<img src="9.jpg" align=left hspace=10 vspace=3 width=150 height=213 border=1>

<b>3. Rooting Out Poverty</b><br>
An examination of the factors which keep 
people in absolute poverty. Shows how the international community is largely failing the world's
poorest people.
<br clear=left>
<p>

<img src="10.jpg" align=left hspace=10 vspace=3 width=150 height=213 border=1>

<b>4. Uncovering the Reality of Aid</b><br>
Summary of evidence gathered by 20 
NGOs worldwide which paints a gloomy picture of government aid to developing countries. June 1993.
<br clear=left>
<p>

<img src="11.jpg" align=left hspace=10 vspace=3 width=150 height=213 border=1>

<b>5. War and Conflict - The price the poorest pay</b><br>
An examination of the costs of conflict on 
the poorest and a critical look at the response of the international community to war and peace.
October 1993.
<br clear=left>
<p>

<img src="12.jpg" align=left hspace=10 vspace=3 width=150 height=213 border=1>

<b>6. Bridging the Poverty Gap</b><br>
A projection of world poverty trends to the 
year 2000. Despite substantial 
improvements, there are worrying signs that the very poorest people are falling further behind. March
1993. 
<br clear=left>
<p>

<img src="13.jpg" align=left hspace=10 vspace=3 width=150 height=213 border=1>
<a name="brief7"></a>
<b>7. Listening to Smaller Voices</b><br>
Executive summary of the full report <i>(see 
<b><a href="#report">Report 2</a></b>),</i> highlighting the importance of involving children in the
planning, 
implementation and evaluation of 
development programming.
<br clear=left>
<p>

<img src="14.jpg" align=left hspace=10 vspace=3 width=150 height=213 border=1>

<b>8. Lessons from Livelihoods</b><br>
Six case studies from Africa, Asia and 
Latin America, illustrating development projects which seek to empower 
communities, meet basic needs and 
care for the environment.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>
</ul>

<p><hr>
