<title>ACTIONAID worker evacuated from Liberia</title>
<!!keys: >
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#000066" vlink="#FF6600">
<a href="../info/index.html"><img src="../pix/logo-t.gif" width=96 height=41 hspace=10
vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a>
<h6 align=left>The material that follows has been provided by <a
href="../info/index.html">ACTIONAID</a></h6><br clear=right>
<br>

<h2 align=center>ACTIONAID worker evacuated from Liberia</h2>


ACTIONAID welcomes the safe return of Peter Crichton, who was evacuated from Liberia in April. 

<p>Peter, from Edinburgh, has been working as ACTIONAID's country representative in Liberia alongside
two other staff since the beginning of March. He says:

<p>
<i>"We're all extremely lucky to have been taken out of Monrovia by the Americans. They launched a
very
impressive evacuation operation. However, our thoughts remain with our local staff members and with
the people of Liberia who are bearing the brunt of this violence. We hope that the country returns to
peace very soon and that aid agencies can get back to work."</i>
<p>

Peter had been researching the potential of a new ACTIONAID programme to rehabilitate primary school
education and to set up a teacher training scheme. Because of the breakdown of security the
assessment mission has been put on hold. However, ACTIONAID will review plans to work in Liberia as
soon
as possible.
<p>

For media enquires only, contact:<br>
Jenny Driscoll, Press Officer on +44 (0) 171 281 4101 or email jennyd@actionaid.org.uk
<hr>
<p>

Find out more about ACTIONAID <b><a href="../info/index.html#help">helping in emergencies</a></b>


<p><b><a href="../lives/index.html">Changing lives:</a></b> find out about the experiences of people
whose lives have
changed with
ACTIONAID's help

