<html><head><title>Development education - investing for the future</title><!!keys: ></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#000066" vlink="#FF6600"><a href="../info/index.html"><img src="../pix/logo-t.gif" width=96 height=41 hspace=10vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><h6 align=left>The material that follows has been provided by <ahref="../info/index.html">ACTIONAID</a></h6><br clear=right><br><h2 align=center>Development education - investing for the future</h2>5.3.96<p>At a time when one fifth of the world's population lives in extreme poverty, development education provides pupils with the skills and knowledge to understand the nature and causes of poverty.<p>In examining the links between rich and poor, North and South, development education equips young people to live in an increasingly interdependent world. Development education increases public awareness of development issues and builds future support for poverty alleviation. However, its funding from government remains very low. <p>According to the latest available figures, the UK spends less on development education than Ireland, whilst Switzerland spends 16 times more and The Netherlands 23 times more than the UK. (Reality of Aid, 1995) <p>Although development education is a statutory part of the National Curriculum in England and Wales, it is buried within the requirements of other subjects, leaving teachers without clear guidelines. ACTIONAID would welcome the opportunity for reports on development education to be a statutory part of inspection visits by the Office for Standards in Education (OFSTED). <p>ACTIONAID welcomes the Overseas Development Administration's (ODA's) interest in working with the Department For Education and Employment (DFEE) on development education issues. Earmarked funding from DFEE could play an essential role in supporting teacher training on development education.<p>Although the ODA is now funding more development education work, most of the funding goes to just one organisation - Worldaware. Extending funds to a wider range of organisations would help advance the work of a number of development agencies, including ACTIONAID, as well as education institutions who produce invaluable development education materials.<p>ACTIONAID's development education work<p>ACTIONAID seeks to increase young people's understanding of poverty in developing countries by publishing education resources and providing a range of services to schools and teachers, particularly in-service training.<p>ACTIONAID's <b><a href="../resource/index.html" target="_parent">resources for teachers</a></b> have received awards from the Geographical Association and the Education Television Association. Teachers have described them as "excellent", "relevant and up-to-date", "exciting and user-friendly".<p>Approximately 1,000,000 pupils in over 50 per cent of schools in England and Wales use ACTIONAID materials every year. <p>ACTIONAID was the first NGO to produce materials to support the 'distant locality' requirements of the geography National Curriculum for 5-11 year olds, and the first to publish a CD-ROM on development issues for schools.<p>It is no coincidence that the countries which have invested in development education also operate high quality aid programmes. Public attitude studies over the years have pointed to the correlation between knowledge about developing countries and positive attitudes towards development co-operation.<hr><p><p><b><a href="../lives/index.html">Changing lives:</a></b> find out about the experiences of people whose lives havechanged withACTIONAID's help<p><hr><p><a href="../home.html"><img src="../pix/home.gif" width=46 height=41 hspace=10vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><a href="../fight/index.html" target="_parent"><img src="../pix/globe1.gif" width=46 height=41hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a> <a href="flashback.html"><img src="../pix/back.gif" width=46height=41hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><font size=1 face=helvetica, arial><b><li type=square><a href="../home.html">Home Page</a> <li type=square><ahref="../fight/index.html" target="_parent">JoinACTIONAID</a> <li type=square><a href="flashback.html">NewsFlashback</a></b></font><br clear=all><p></body></html>
