ay"><h3> Autumn/Winter 1994 - issue 19 </h3></font><ul><p> <li type=square><b><a href="coca1/home.html">Holding on to home </a></b><br>Life in the Peruvian Andes can be hard, so why should the young stay? The people of Llactun tell their story.<p> <li type=square><b><a href="coca1/tradition.html">Building on tradition </a></b><br>The village elders in rural Pakistan are used to making the decisions, so when building a new water supply scheme affects everyone, how do others get a say?<p> <li type=square><b><a href="coca1/taboos.html">Talking taboos </a></b><br>The villagers of Ayakoliga, Ghana, talk about the traditions and taboos that govern their lives and the threat of modern ways, including those of ACTIONAID.</ul><p><hr><p><a href="../home.html"><img src="../pix/home.gif" width=46 height=41hspace=10vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><a href="index.html" target="_parent"><img src="../pix/globe1.gif" width=46height=41hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><font size=1 face=helvetica, arial><li type=square><b><a href="../home.html">Home Page</a></b><li type=square> <b><a href="index.html" target="_parent">JoinACTIONAID</a></b></font><br clear=all><p></body></html><p>
